 Police have made aÂ breakthrough following a series of burglaries at guesthouses in King Williams Town. According to police spokesperson, Captain Siphokazi Mawisa, a team was assigned to investigate these incidences managed to arrest a man with property stolen from the guesthouses. "On Thursday night, a 25-year-old male from Ginsberg, near Kingwilliamstown was arrested. "Police followed up the information and last night an electronic equipment worth over R30 000.00 was recovered," she said. "The suspect is due to appear at King Williams Town Magistrate's Court soon in charges of Business Burglary." 